Name: SMC Message Registry
Description: This registry defines the OEM messages for Redfish

OemUserNotToEnableOneDisabledService.Description: Indicates that the user cannot change any other settings except for enabling the disabled service.
OemUserNotToEnableOneDisabledService.Message: Disabled service %1 was not allowed the user to change settings without enabling it.
OemUserNotToEnableOneDisabledService.Resolution: Enable it or you cannot change any other settings.

OemAdMissingItem.Description: Indicates that a required item was not supplied as part of the request.
OemAdMissingItem.Message: To enable Active Directory authentication must have at least one server IP setting.
OemAdMissingItem.Resolution: Add one domain control server IP.

OemAdPatchSettingCondition.Description: Indicates that a must require property was not supplied as part of the request.
OemAdPatchSettingCondition.Message: To set the required information to access the Active Directory, user must enable Active Directory Authentication.

OemSmtpModified.Description: Indicates that the SMTP settings were successfully changed.

OemRadiusModified.Description: Indicates that the RADIUS settings were successfully changed.

OemOtherAuthenticationServiceIsRunning.Description: Indicates that other authentication services were running.
OemOtherAuthenticationServiceIsRunning.Message: %1 authentication service was already enabled, so %2 cannot be enabled.
OemOtherAuthenticationServiceIsRunning.Resolution: Disable other authentication services and then try again.

OemOnlyOneAuthenticationServiceCanBeEnab.Description: Indicates that only one authentication service can be enabled.
OemOnlyOneAuthenticationServiceCanBeEnab.Message: Only one authentication service can be enabled.

OemAdInvalidPortNumberWithoutSsl.Description: Indicates that an invalid port in request with the SSL is being disabled.
OemAdInvalidPortNumberWithoutSsl.Message: The value %1 for the property %2 was an invalid port number with the SSL being disabled.
OemAdInvalidPortNumberWithoutSsl.Resolution: Only 389 or 3268 port can be supported with the SSL being disabled.

OemAdInvalidPortNumberWithSsl.Description: Indicates that an invalid port in request with the SSL being enabled.
OemAdInvalidPortNumberWithSsl.Message: The value %1 for the property %2 was an invalid port number with the SSL being enabled.
OemAdInvalidPortNumberWithSsl.Resolution: Only 636 or 3269 port can be supported with the SSL being enabled.

OemNtpPatchSettingCondition.Description: Indicates that to set the required information, user needs to enable the NTP first.
OemNtpPatchSettingCondition.Message: To set the required information to access the NTP server, user must enable the NTP first.

OemIllegalGroupName.Description: Indicates that there were special characters in the request to set the domain name.
OemIllegalGroupName.Message: In %1 property, following special characters are not allowed: ,; &\"<>=$*!@~`%^#
OemIllegalGroupName.Resolution: Do not include special characters in the group name.

OemIllegalDomainName.Description: Indicates that there were special characters in the request to set the domain name.
OemIllegalDomainName.Message: In %1 property, following special characters are not allowed: ,;&'\"<>=$|^?*~`()[]#%{}
OemIllegalDomainName.Resolution: Do not include special characters in the domain name.

OemNtpMissingItem.Description: Indicates that a required property was not supplied as part of the request to enable the NTP.
OemNtpMissingItem.Message: To enable, the NTP must have at least one setting.

OemNtpAcceptedMessage.Description: Indicate that request to configure NTP was accepted successfully but it takes time to perform.
OemNtpAcceptedMessage.Message: Please also check Task Resource %1 to see more information.

OemMousemodeModified.Description: Indicates that the Mouse Mode was successfully modified.

OemIkvmInterfaceModified.Description: Indicates that the iKVM interface was successfully modified.

TaskMonitorException.Description: Task monitor exception occurred, please see below for more details.
TaskMonitorException.Resolution: Please check if anything wrong and do it again.

TaskMonitorAccepted.Description: Task monitor was running, please see below for more details.

TaskMonitorCompleted.Description: Task monitor was completed, please see below for more details.

OemFailModifyLanSetting.Description: Indicate that the LAN setting was failed.
OemFailModifyLanSetting.Message: Modication of the LAN setting was failed due to the LAN information was unable to obtain.

OemFailSetLanspeed.Description: Indicate that set LAN speed only when the LAN cable was plugged in the Dedicated port.
OemFailSetLanspeed.Message: Right now the LAN cable was not plugged in the Dedicated port hence the LAN speed was not configurable.
OemFailSetLanspeed.Resolution: Plug the LAN cable to the Dedicate port.

OemLanspeedUnsupported.Description: Indicate set LAN speed failed due to invalid value.

OemLdapModified.Description: Indicate that the LDAP was successfully configured.

OemLdapInvalidPortNumberWithoutSsl.Description: Indicate that the LDAP port setting needs attention.
OemLdapInvalidPortNumberWithoutSsl.Message: The value %1 for the property %2 was an invalid number with the SSL being disabled.
OemLdapInvalidPortNumberWithoutSsl.Resolution: Only 389 port can be supported with the SSL being disabled.

OemLdapInvalidPortNumberWithSsl.Description: Indicate that the LDAP port setting needs attention.
OemLdapInvalidPortNumberWithSsl.Message: The value %1 for the property %2 was an invalid number with the SSL being enabled.
OemLdapInvalidPortNumberWithSsl.Resolution: Only 636 port can be supported with the SSL being enabled.

OemLdapBadServiceAddresses.Description: Indicate that the LDAP service address needs attention.
OemLdapBadServiceAddresses.Message: The value %1 for the property %2 was an invalid service address.
OemLdapBadServiceAddresses.Resolution: Service addresses should start with ldap:// or ldaps://.

OemLdapBadIpAddresses.Description: Indicate that the IP address needs to attention.
OemLdapBadIpAddresses.Message: It's an illegal IP address format.
OemLdapBadIpAddresses.Resolution: IP address should match the valid IP format.

OemLdapBadPortNumber.Description: Indicate that the port number needs attention.
OemLdapBadPortNumber.Message: It's an illegal port number format.
OemLdapBadPortNumber.Resolution: Port number should match the valid port format.

OemLdapBadLocalRole.Description: Indicate that the local role needs to be corrected.
OemLdapBadLocalRole.Message: The value %1 for the property %2 is an invalid local role.
OemLdapBadLocalRole.Resolution: Local role should be one of the following: Administrator, Operator, or User.

OemSmcrakpModified.Description: Indicate that the RAKP was successfully configured.

OemSyslogModified.Description: Indicate that the Syslog was successfully configured.

OemIpAccessControlDisabled.Description: Indicate that the filtering rule was able to be added only when service was running.
OemIpAccessControlDisabled.Message: To set the filtering rule, must enable the IP Access Control Service first.
OemIpAccessControlDisabled.Resolution: Enable the IP Access Control Service first and try again.

OemIpAccessControlRefuseLocal.Description: Indicate that accept policy with localhost is the default setting in the IP table.
OemIpAccessControlRefuseLocal.Message: The accept policy with localhost %1 is the default setting in the IP table.
OemIpAccessControlRefuseLocal.Resolution: Enter the other valid IP address instead of localhost.

OemVmCdcfgModified.Description: Indicate that the Virtual Media was successfully configured.
OemVmCdcfgModified.Message: The Virtual Media was configured successfully.

OemVmMounted.Description: Indicate that the Virtual Media was successfully mounted.
OemVmMounted.Message: The Virtual Media was mounted successfully.

OemVmMountFail.Description: Indicate that the Virtual Media was failed to mount.
OemVmMountFail.Resolution: Check the Virtual Media settings and the connection to share point.

OemVmUnmounted.Description: Indicate that the Virtual Media was successfully unmounted.
OemVmUnmounted.Message: The Virtual Media was unmounted successfully.

OemVmUnmountFail.Description: Indicate that the Virtual Media was failed to unmount.
OemVmUnmountFail.Resolution: Check if the Virtual Media was in use.

OemVmImageEmpty.Description: Indicate that the Virtual Media Image was empty.
OemVmImageEmpty.Message: Please enter the location for the virtual media image.

OemVmImageIpv6Linklocal.Description: Indicate that the IPv6 link-local address was not suitable for Virtual Media.
OemVmImageIpv6Linklocal.Message: The IPv6 link-local address was not allowed.

OemVmPathEmpty.Description: Indicate that the Virtual Media path was empty.
OemVmPathEmpty.Message: Please enter the path to the image.

OemVmPathError.Description: Indicate that the Virtual Media path was invalid.
OemVmPathError.Message: The path did not meet the expected pattern. (It is not an ISO file or contains :*?\"<>|).

OemVmUserPassEmptyError.Description: Indicate that the Virtual Media User or password was empty.
OemVmUserPassEmptyError.Message: Virtual Media User and password should be either both filled or both empty at the same time.
OemVmUserPassEmptyError.Resolution: Fill or empty both user and password concurrently.

OemSnmpModified.Description: Indicate that the SNMP was successfully configured.

OemSnmpv2Modified.Description: Indicate that the SNMPv2 was successfully configured.

OemSnmpv3Modified.Description: Indicate that the SNMPv3 was successfully configured.

OemSnmpv3IllegalKey.Description: Indicate that an invalid key was used.
OemSnmpv3IllegalKey.Message: At least 8 characters are necessary and it must contain lowercase letters, uppercase letters, and numbers.
OemSnmpv3IllegalKey.Resolution: Revise key pattern and try again.

OemSnmpv3IllegalProtocolType.Description: Indicate that the incorrect protocol type was used.
OemSnmpv3IllegalProtocolType.Message: Incorrect protocol type for the SNMPv3.

OemSnmpv3EmptyUser.Description: Indicate that the user field was empty.
OemSnmpv3EmptyUser.Message: This user field cannot be empty for the SNMPv3.

OemSnmpv3IllegalUser.Description: Indicate that there were special characters in the request to set the user name.
OemSnmpv3IllegalUser.Message: The user field for SNMPv3 cannot contain: ,;&'\"<>=$|^?*~`()[]#%{}.
OemSnmpv3IllegalUser.Resolution: Do not include special characters in the SNMPv3 user name.

OemSslcertUploaded.Description: Indicate that the SSL certificate and private key were successfully uploaded.
OemSslcertUploaded.Message: SSL certificate and private key were successfully uploaded.

OemSslcertMissingItem.Description: Indicate that wrong files were uploaded.
OemSslcertMissingItem.Message: Upload files should have the private key and SSL certificate, please put the correct values in the POST key fields.
OemSslcertMissingItem.Resolution: Check the key value of the POST method for those two upload files.

OemSslcertIllegalPair.Description: Indicate that uploaded files were not matching to activate the SSL.
OemSslcertIllegalPair.Message: The certificate and private key files should be a pair.
OemSslcertIllegalPair.Resolution: Check those two upload files and try again.

OemHttppushuriErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that something wrong on HttpPushUri.
OemHttppushuriErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check the reason for the error.

OemActivatelicenseErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that something wrong on ActivateLicense.
OemActivatelicenseErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check the reason for the error.

OemHttppushuriAcceptedMessage.Description: Indicate that request was accepted and it took some time to update.
OemHttppushuriAcceptedMessage.Message: Please check Task Resource %1 to see more information.

OemSimpleupdateErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that something wrong on SimpleUpdate.

OemSimpleupdateAcceptedMessage.Description: Indicate that request was accepted and it took some time to update.
OemSimpleupdateAcceptedMessage.Message: Please also check Task Resource %1 to see more information.

OemSimpleupdatePmemAcceptedMessage.Description: Indicate that request was accepted and it took some time to update.
OemSimpleupdatePmemAcceptedMessage.Message: Please also check Task Resource %1 to see more information.
OemSimpleupdatePmemAcceptedMessage.Resolution: Please perform system reset in order to finish PMem FW update!

OemIndicateDriveLedAcceptedMessage.Description: Indicate that request to turn on/off drive indicator was accepted successfully but it took some time to perform.
OemIndicateDriveLedAcceptedMessage.Message: Please check Task Resource %1 to see more information.

OemIndicateDriveLedErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that request to turn on/off drive indicator was unsuccessful.
OemIndicateDriveLedErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check the error for reason(s).

OemPortInUse.Description: Indicate that the port number was occupied.
OemPortInUse.Message: The port number %1 was in use.
OemPortInUse.Resolution: Please change to another port number.

OemKvmServiceDisabled.Description: Indicate that current setting was failed to apply due to the KVM service was not enabled.
OemKvmServiceDisabled.Message: The KVM service was disabled hence %1 can't be enabled.
OemKvmServiceDisabled.Resolution: Please enable the KVM service first and try again.

OemPlatformNotSupportFanModeModify.Description: Indicate that this FAN mode cannot be modified.
OemPlatformNotSupportFanModeModify.Message: This platform doesn't support Fan Mode modify.

AccountLockup.Description: Indicate that the current account was locked up.
AccountLockup.Resolution: Please wait until the account is unlocked.

OemBasicAuthApplyIkvmFail.Description: Indicate that it failed at application for the iKVM URI to launch.
OemBasicAuthApplyIkvmFail.Resolution: Please check if you have acquired a valid session or wait for previous a validated session being timeout then acquire again.

OemStorageHaRaidSaved.Description: Indicate that the setting for storage controller was successfully saved.

OemStorageLocated.Description: Indicate that the drive indicator was successfully located/unlocated.

OemStorageVolumeWrongParam.Description: Indicate that the volume creation was failed when wrong parameters were used.
OemStorageVolumeWrongParam.Message: Wrong parameters %s were used to create the volume.
OemStorageVolumeWrongParam.Resolution: Please use allowable values to create a volume.

OemStorageVolumeCreateFail.Description: Indicate that the volume creation was failed.
OemStorageVolumeCreateFail.Message: Creation of volume was failed, please check the input parameters.
OemStorageVolumeCreateFail.Resolution: Please verify if input parameters are correct and try again.

OemStorageConfigPatchFail.Description: Indicate wrong parameters for the configuration of the storage controller.
OemStorageConfigPatchFail.Resolution: Please check if anything was OK and try it again.

OemStorageDeleted.Description: Indicate that the volume was successfully deleted.

OemStorageVolumeCreated.Description: Indicate that the volume was successfully created.

OemStorageVolumeDeleted.Description: Indicate that the volume was successfully deleted.

OemStorageVolumeRebuild.Description: Indicate that the volume was successfully rebuild.

OemStorageDriveUnmarkSpare.Description: Indicate that the drive was successfully unmark spare.
OemStorageDriveUnmarkSpare.Message: The drive was successfully unmark spare.

OemBiosUpdateIsInProgress.Description: Indicate that there was already one BIOS image was updating.
OemBiosUpdateIsInProgress.Message: The BIOS Update was in progress.
OemBiosUpdateIsInProgress.Resolution: The BIOS was updating and please wait till it was finished.

OemBiosUpdateNoImage.Description: Indicate that there was no BIOS image uploaded to perform image updating.
OemBiosUpdateNoImage.Message: No BIOS image to update, please upload first.
OemBiosUpdateNoImage.Resolution: Please upload a BIOS image and try again.

OemBiosUpdateWrongImage.Description: Indicate that a wrong BIOS was uploaded to perform updating.
OemBiosUpdateWrongImage.Message: Unable to recognize the BIOS image content.
OemBiosUpdateWrongImage.Resolution: Please upload a valid BIOS firmware image and try again.

OemBiosUpdateErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the BIOS updating was failed due to a possible error below.
OemBiosUpdateErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check this error reason and try again.

OemUnknownFirmwareType.Description: Indicate that an unknown firmware was chosen to perform updating.
OemUnknownFirmwareType.Resolution: Please verify that the current firmware type is supported to perform updating.

OemFirmwareUpdateIsInProgress.Description: Indicate that there was already one BMC firmware was updating.
OemFirmwareUpdateIsInProgress.Message: The BMC firmware Update was in progress.
OemFirmwareUpdateIsInProgress.Resolution: The BMC was updating and please wait until it was finished.

OemFirmwareUpdateNoImage.Description: Indicate that there was no BMC firmware uploaded to perform updating.
OemFirmwareUpdateNoImage.Message: No BMC image to update, please upload first.
OemFirmwareUpdateNoImage.Resolution: Please upload a BMC firmware and try again.

OemFirmwareAlreadyInUpdateMode.Description: Indicate that a duplicated Enter Update Mode was performed.
OemFirmwareAlreadyInUpdateMode.Message: The %1 firmware update was already in update mode.
OemFirmwareAlreadyInUpdateMode.Resolution: Please check if there was the next step with respective API to execute.

OemFirmwareNotInUpdateMode.Description: Indicate that the BMC firmware update was not following the correct procedure to perform updating.
OemFirmwareNotInUpdateMode.Message: The BMC firmware update was not in update mode.
OemFirmwareNotInUpdateMode.Resolution: Please execute Enter Update Mode and try again.

OemFirmwareUpdateWrongImage.Description: Indicate that the BMC firmware image content checking failed thus firmware updating process was stopped.
OemFirmwareUpdateWrongImage.Message: The BMC firmware image content was not recognized so the update was stopped.
OemFirmwareUpdateWrongImage.Resolution: Please upload a valid BMC firmware image and try again.

OemFirmwareUpdateErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the BMC firmware update fails due to something.
OemFirmwareUpdateErrorMessage.Message: BMC firmware update process has failed.
OemFirmwareUpdateErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check if there was anything wrong and try again.

OemFileDownloaded.Description: Indicate that the file was downloaded successfully. Please keep as a backup.

OemFileDownloadErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the file was not found and was not downloaded.
OemFileDownloadErrorMessage.Message: Failed to download the selected file %1.
OemFileDownloadErrorMessage.Resolution: Please verify everything then try again.

OemNotFromHostInterfaceErrorMessage.Description: Request should be from Host Interface
OemNotFromHostInterfaceErrorMessage.Resolution: Request should be from Host Interface.

OemIpmiConfigRestored.Description: Indicate that the uploaded IPMI configuration was accepted and restored. It will soon cause BMC automatically to reboot in order to restore the configuration.
OemIpmiConfigRestored.Message: The IPMI configuration was successfully restored. BMC will be rebooted shortly.

OemIpmiConfigRestoreErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the IPMI configuration could not be restored currently.
OemIpmiConfigRestoreErrorMessage.Message: Failed to restore the selected IPMI configuration.
OemIpmiConfigRestoreErrorMessage.Resolution: Please try again with a different configuration file.

OemIpmiConfigMissingItem.Description: Indicate that the necessary key was not uploaded with the IPMI configuration.
OemIpmiConfigMissingItem.Message: The uploaded file should be a saved IPMI configuration file. Please put correct value in the POST key field.
OemIpmiConfigMissingItem.Resolution: Check the key value of the POST method for the uploaded file.

OemLicenseNotPassed.Description: Indicate that the privilege checking was failed.
OemLicenseNotPassed.Message: Not licensed to perform this request. The following licenses %1 were needed
OemLicenseNotPassed.Resolution: Please activate at least one license in the above message.

OemNmAllPoliciesCleared.Description: Indicate that all NM policies were successfully cleared.
OemNmAllPoliciesCleared.Message: NM all policies were successfully cleared.

OemNmAllPoliciesClearFail.Description: Indicate that all NM policies clearing were failed.
OemNmAllPoliciesClearFail.Message: Failed to clear NM all policies.
OemNmAllPoliciesClearFail.Resolution: Please make sure CPU types were correct to support clear NM policies.

OemActiveNmSet.Description: Indicate that active node manager is set.

OemSetActiveNmFailed.Description: Indicate that set active node manager were failed.
OemSetActiveNmFailed.Message: Failed to set active node manager.
OemSetActiveNmFailed.Resolution: Please make sure NM Target types were correct to active..

OemSyslockdownModified.Description: Indicate that the System Lockdown was successfully configured.
OemSyslockdownModified.Message: The System Lockdown was successfully modified.
OemSyslockdownModified.Resolution: Please reset the system for the system lock control operation to take effect.

OemMemorypfaModified.Description: Indicate that the memory PFA was successfully configured.
OemMemorypfaModified.Message: The memory PFA was successfully modified.
OemMemorypfaModified.Resolution: Please reset the system for the memory PFA control operation to take effect.

OemMemoryhealthcompModified.Description: Indicate that the memory health components was successfully configured.
OemMemoryhealthcompModified.Message: The memory health components was successfully modified.
OemMemoryhealthcompModified.Resolution: Please reset the system for the memory health components control operation to take effect.

OemMarkAsAcknowledged.Description: Indicates that the event was successfully marked to acknowledge.

OemSystemLockdownEnabled.Description: Indicate that the System Lockdown was enabled.
OemSystemLockdownEnabled.Message: System is in lockdown mode. This action is forbidden.

OemSystemLockdownEnabledPatchValid.Description: Indicate that the System Lockdown was enabled.
OemSystemLockdownEnabledPatchValid.Message: The System Lockdown was turned on, only support patch %1.

OemFileoperationErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the file operation has an error.

OemPlatformNotSupportNodeManager.Description: Indicate that there is no node manager in this platform.
OemPlatformNotSupportNodeManager.Message: This platform doesn't support Node Manager.

OemActionFailDueToIPProtocolStatus.Description: Indicates that IP Protocol Status doesn't allow this change.
OemActionFailDueToIPProtocolStatus.Message: Due to IP Protocol Status is %1, you can do any changes for %2

OemSecureEraseIsInProgress.Description: Indicate that a secure erase action was in progress.
OemSecureEraseIsInProgress.Message: Secure Erase action is in progress.
OemSecureEraseIsInProgress.Resolution: Secure Erase action is in progress. Please wait until the action is completed.

OemSecureEraseIsNotInProgress.Description: Indicate that there was no secure erase action was performed.
OemSecureEraseIsNotInProgress.Message: Secure Erase action is not in progress.

OemSecureEraseIsInProgressWithTaskId.Description: Indicate that a secure erase was being performed.
OemSecureEraseIsInProgressWithTaskId.Message: Secure Erase action is in progress and please check Task Resource %1 to see more information.
OemSecureEraseIsInProgressWithTaskId.Resolution: Secure Erase action is in progress. Please wait until the action is completed.

OemSecureEraseAcceptedMessage.Description: Indicate that the request to perform secure erase was accepted successfully but it will take some time to perform.
OemSecureEraseAcceptedMessage.Message: Please check Task Resource %1 to see more information.

OemSecureEraseAbortAcceptedMessage.Description: Indicate that the request to abort secure erase was accepted successfully.
OemSecureEraseAbortAcceptedMessage.Message: Secure Erase action was successfully aborted.

OemSecureEraseErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that request to perform or abort secure erase was unable to do.
OemSecureEraseErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check error for the reason.

OemTaskServiceDisabledMessage.Description: Indicate that the TaskService was disabled and the Task Resource was not provided.
OemTaskServiceDisabledMessage.Message: The TaskService was disabled so the Task Resource was not provided.

OemReservedIpv4Address.Description: Indicates that a reserved IP address was requested.
OemReservedIpv4Address.Message: The value %1 with a subnet mask of %2 for the property %3 is a reserved IP.
OemReservedIpv4Address.Resolution: Please set a new IP address on another network segment.

OemCpldAlreadyInUpdateMode.Description: Indicate that a device update is already in progress.
OemCpldAlreadyInUpdateMode.Message: BMC is already in update mode.
OemCpldAlreadyInUpdateMode.Resolution: Please check if there was the next step with respective API to execute.

OemCpldUpdateNoImage.Description: Indicate that there is no update image uploaded to perform the device firmware update.
OemCpldUpdateNoImage.Message: No %1 image was uploaded, please upload a firmware image first.

OemCpldUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Description: Indicate that device update is not in update mode.
OemCpldUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Message: The %1 firmware update is not in update mode.
OemCpldUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Resolution: Please execute Enter Update Mode and try again.

OemCpldUpdateIsInProgress.Description: Indicate that a device update is already in progress.
OemCpldUpdateIsInProgress.Message: The %1 Update is already in progress.
OemCpldUpdateIsInProgress.Resolution: A device is being updated. Please wait until the process is completed.

OemCpldUpdateErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the update process failed due to possible errors below.
OemCpldUpdateErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check the error and re-run the process again.

OemHgxAlreadyInUpdateMode.Description: Indicate that a device update is already in progress.
OemHgxAlreadyInUpdateMode.Message: BMC is already in update mode.
OemHgxAlreadyInUpdateMode.Resolution: Please check if there was the next step with respective API to execute.

OemHgxUpdateIsInProgress.Description: Indicate that a device update is already in progress.
OemHgxUpdateIsInProgress.Message: The %1 Update is already in progress.
OemHgxUpdateIsInProgress.Resolution: A device is updating and please wait till it is finished.

OemHgxUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Description: Indicate that device update is not in update mode.
OemHgxUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Message: The %1 firmware update is not in update mode.
OemHgxUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Resolution: Please execute Enter Update Mode and do it again.

OemHgxUpdateNoImage.Description: Indicate that there is no update image uploaded to perform the device firmware update.
OemHgxUpdateNoImage.Message: No %1 image uploaded, please upload first.

OemHgxTypeNotSupport.Description: Indicate that firmware update on this HGX A100 board type is not supported.
OemHgxTypeNotSupport.Message: Firmware update on HGX A100 %1 board is not supported.

OemBrcmUpdateIsInProgress.Description: Indicate that a BRCM image is updating.
OemBrcmUpdateIsInProgress.Message: The BRCM %1 Update is in progress.
OemBrcmUpdateIsInProgress.Resolution: The BRCM is updating. Please wait until the process is completed.

OemBrcmUpdateNoImage.Description: Indicate that there was no BRCM image was uploaded to perform updating.
OemBrcmUpdateNoImage.Message: No BRCM image to update. Please upload a BRCM image first.
OemBrcmUpdateNoImage.Resolution: Please upload a BRCM image and try again.

OemBrcmUpdateErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the BRCM updating was failed due to a possible error below.
OemBrcmUpdateErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check the possible reason and try again.

OemMrvlUpdateIsInProgress.Description: Indicate that an MRVL image is in the updating process.
OemMrvlUpdateIsInProgress.Message: The MRVL %1 Update was in progress.
OemMrvlUpdateIsInProgress.Resolution: The MRVL storage controller is being updated. Please wait until the process is completed.

OemMrvlUpdateNoImage.Description: Indicate that there was no MRVL image being uploaded to perform updating.
OemMrvlUpdateNoImage.Message: No MRVL image to update, please upload an MRVL image first.
OemMrvlUpdateNoImage.Resolution: Please upload an MRVL image and try again.

OemMrvlUpdateErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the MRVL updating process had failed due to a possible error below.
OemMrvlUpdateErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check the possible reason and try again.

OemAntiRollForward.Description: Indicates that the Rollback ID of the new firmware is higher than the current one in the system.
OemAntiRollForward.Message: The Rollback ID of the new firmware is higher than the current one in the system.

OemEvidenceDumpErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the evidence dump process had failed due to a possible error below.
OemEvidenceDumpErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check the possible reason and try again.

OemRequestAcceptedMessage.Description: Indicate that request was accepted successfully but it takes time to perform.
OemRequestAcceptedMessage.Message: Please also check Task Resource %1 to see more information.

OemIpv6DefaultGatewayConfigureFail.Description: Indicates that configuration for IPv6 default gateway is failed
OemIpv6DefaultGatewayConfigureFail.Resolution: Please help to check this address is reachable.

OemNicUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Description: Indicate that device update is not in update mode.
OemNicUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Message: The %1 firmware update is not in update mode.
OemNicUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Resolution: Please execute Enter Update Mode and do it again.

OemNicUpdateIsInProgress.Description: Indicate that there was already one NIC image was updating.
OemNicUpdateIsInProgress.Message: The NIC %1 Update was in progress.
OemNicUpdateIsInProgress.Resolution: The NIC was updating and please wait till it was finished.

OemNicUpdateNoImage.Description: Indicate that there was no NIC image being uploaded to continue performing updating.
OemNicUpdateNoImage.Message: No NIC image to update, please upload first.
OemNicUpdateNoImage.Resolution: Please upload an NIC image and do it again.

OemNicUpdateErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the NIC updating was failed due to a possible error below.
OemNicUpdateErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check this error reason and run it again.

OemGpuUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Description: Indicate that device update is not in update mode.
OemGpuUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Message: The %1 firmware update is not in update mode.
OemGpuUpdateNotInUpdateMode.Resolution: Please execute Enter Update Mode and do it again.

OemGpuUpdateIsInProgress.Description: Indicate that there was already one GPU image was updating.
OemGpuUpdateIsInProgress.Message: The GPU %1 Update was in progress.
OemGpuUpdateIsInProgress.Resolution: The GPU was updating and please wait till it was finished.

OemGpuUpdateNoImage.Description: Indicate that there was no GPU image being uploaded to continue performing updating.
OemGpuUpdateNoImage.Message: No GPU image to update, please upload first.
OemGpuUpdateNoImage.Resolution: Please upload an GPU image and do it again.

OemGpuUpdateErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the GPU updating was failed due to a possible error below.
OemGpuUpdateErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check this error reason and run it again.

OemRequestDataDuplicate.Description: Indicates that operation cannot proceed because there are two or more same requested data.
OemRequestDataDuplicate.Resolution: Do not repeat the requested data for this resource.

OemUserNotToDisabledServiceWhenUserLogin.Description: Indicates that the user cannot disable service when there is an directory service user who have logined.
OemUserNotToDisabledServiceWhenUserLogin.Message: Disabled service %1 was not allowed there is an directory service user who have logined.
OemUserNotToDisabledServiceWhenUserLogin.Resolution: Kill all related session or Wait these users logout.

OemUserDisableFail.Description: Indicates that the user cannot be disabled or deleted, because there is an session activated by this user.
OemUserDisableFail.Message: The User %1 cannot be disabled or deleted, because there is an active session created by this user.
OemUserDisableFail.Resolution: Logout the session and try disable action again.

OemNetworkProtocolAcceptedMessage.Description: Indicate that request was accepted successfully but it takes time to perform.
OemNetworkProtocolAcceptedMessage.Message: Please also check Task Resource %1 to see more information.

OemPortInTcpWaitTimeState.Description: Indicate that the port number was occupied.
OemPortInTcpWaitTimeState.Message: TCP WAIT_TIME State: Please wait for a moment until the port %1 becomes available. If problem persists, please check whether port is in the use.
OemPortInTcpWaitTimeState.Resolution: Please change to another port number or wait for few minutes.

OemSmtpPatchSettingCondition.Description: Indicates that a must require property was not supplied as part of the request.
OemSmtpPatchSettingCondition.Message: To set the required information to access the SMTP, user must enable SMTP Authentication.

OemSmtpSettingNotAllow.Description: Indicates that SMTP Server setting is not allowed.
OemSmtpSettingNotAllow.Message: Choosing 'None' for ConnectionProtocol and 'AutoDetect' for AuthenticationProtocol is not supported simultaneously.

OemBiosUploadFail.Description: Indicates that there's a New BIOS fw is loaded into Staging Region (NAND device) and will be transferred to BIOS NOR Flash region upon system reset.
OemBiosUploadFail.Message: There's a New BIOS fw is loaded into Staging Region and will be transferred to BIOS NOR Flash region upon system reset.
OemBiosUploadFail.Resolution: If want to cancel the staging update for BIOS, to delete the pending task in task service

OemAssignSpare.Description: Indicate that the drive was assigned to HotSpare drive.

OemDeleteSpare.Description: Indicate that the HotSpare drive was removed.

OemTeeFileUploadMissingItem.Description: Indicate that the necessary key was not uploaded with the Tee File upload.
OemTeeFileUploadMissingItem.Message: The uploaded file should be a saved binary file. Please put correct value in the POST key field.
OemTeeFileUploadMissingItem.Resolution: Check the key value of the POST method for the uploaded file.

OemTeeFileUpdateErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the update process failed due to possible errors below.
OemTeeFileUpdateErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check the error and re-run the process again.

CertainConfigurationNotSet.Description: Indicates that some header settings was not set
CertainConfigurationNotSet.Message: A certain configuration is required for access resources

SettingsSuccess.Description: Indicates the settings are successfully acceptable.

SettingsFailed.Description: Indicates some attributes are not acceptable.
SettingsFailed.Resolution: Check if these attributes are acceptable or not

NotSupportSecureboot.Message: Current BIOS does not support Secureboot functionalities, please use supported BIOS and try again.

LicenseClearFailed.Description: Indicates the product key doesn't exist.
LicenseClearFailed.Resolution: Please check the product key does exist or not.

NetworkProtocolServiceConfigureFailed.Description: Indicates that NetworkProtocol configuration is not allowed in current state.
NetworkProtocolServiceConfigureFailed.Message: %1 %2 Service is not allowed, because user configure it to the same setting as current.
NetworkProtocolServiceConfigureFailed.Resolution: Please check the service current settings.

OemDrivesmartDumpErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the smart dump process had failed due to a possible error below.
OemDrivesmartDumpErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check the possible reason and try again.

OemUpdateActionNotSupported.Description: It indicates that this Redfish API will be removed from X13-and-after platforms.
OemUpdateActionNotSupported.Message: It is NOT recommended to use this API, because this Redfish API is obsolete. Supermicro considers removing this API from X13-and-after platforms.
OemUpdateActionNotSupported.Resolution: Please use the standard Redfish API to update firmware. URI://redfish/v1/UpdateService/FirmwareInventory/upload.

OemRaProvisionMessage.Resolution: Please forward this message to RD.

OemNvmeUpdateIsInProgress.Description: Indicate that a NVMe drive FW image is updating.
OemNvmeUpdateIsInProgress.Message: The NVMe Drive Update of BPN %1 CPLD %2 SLOT %3 is in progress.
OemNvmeUpdateIsInProgress.Resolution: The NVMe Drive of BPN %1 CPLD %2 SLOT %3 is updating. Please wait until the process is completed.

OemNvmeUpdateNoImage.Description: Indicate that there was no NVMe drive FW image was uploaded to perform updating.
OemNvmeUpdateNoImage.Message: No NVMe drive FW image to update. Please upload a NVMe drive FW image first.
OemNvmeUpdateNoImage.Resolution: Please upload a NVMe drive FW image and try again.

OemNvmeUpdateErrorMessage.Description: Indicate that the NVMe drive updating was failed due to a possible error below.
OemNvmeUpdateErrorMessage.Resolution: Please check the possible reason and try again.

OemIPMIServiceDisabled.Description: Indicate that current setting was failed to apply due to the IPMI service was not enabled.
OemIPMIServiceDisabled.Message: The IPMI service was disabled hence %1 can't be enabled.
OemIPMIServiceDisabled.Resolution: Please enable the IPMI service first and try again.

OemPropertyModifySuggested.Description: It indicates which Redfish API to modify property is suggested.
OemPropertyModifySuggested.Message: It is NOT recommended to use this API to modify %1, because this property is inherited from another. Please use the URI:%2 Property:%3 alternative.
OemPropertyModifySuggested.Resolution: Please use the recommended Redfish API to modify

OemApiObsolete.Description: It indicates that this Redfish API will be removed.
OemApiObsolete.Message: It is NOT recommended to use this API, because this Redfish API is obsolete. Supermicro considers removing this API from %1-and-after platforms. Please use the URI:%2 alternative.
OemApiObsolete.Resolution: Please use the standard Redfish API.

OemServiceDisabled.Description: Indicate that the Service was not able to operate when Service disabled.
OemServiceDisabled.Message: To operate the %1, must enable the %2 first.
OemServiceDisabled.Resolution: Enable the Service first and try again.
